  <chunk id="54ebc03fe88092d143f0758472adf54252d6c224.c0" text="Free fatty acids induce ER stress and block antiviral activity of interferon alpha against hepatitis C virus in cell culture">
    <entity charOffset="91-100" id="54ebc03fe88092d143f0758472adf54252d6c224.c0.e0" ontology_id="HP_0012115" text="hepatitis" type="phenotype"/>
  </chunk>
  <chunk id="54ebc03fe88092d143f0758472adf54252d6c224.c1" text="Background: Hepatic steatosis is recognized as a major risk factor for liver disease progression and impaired response to interferon based therapy in chronic hepatitis C (CHC) patients. The mechanism of response to interferon-alpha (IFN-α) therapy under the condition of hepatic steatosis is unexplored. We investigated the effect of hepatocellular steatosis on hepatitis C virus (HCV) replication and IFN-α antiviral response in a cell culture model.">
